---
name: data-modeling-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for data modeling in knowledge graphs
globs: **/*.jsonl
---

- Normalize attributes and relationships to reduce redundancy and improve data integrity.
- Clearly define node and relationship types to facilitate easier querying and understanding.
- Use descriptive names for nodes and relationships to enhance readability.
- Document the data model schema to ensure clarity for future developers.
- Regularly review and update the schema as the application evolves.
